just_use claude_landing.go

# label: SPIKE (ANCHOR_COMMENTS stack)
# role: Gopher view — the /gopher/claude landing page

One-page sub-landing that sits between Gopher's home and
Claude-owned sub-tools (Essays, Issues). Two-card layout
linking to:

- `/gopher/essays` — Steve's long-form writing with inline
  paragraph comments
- `/gopher/claude-issues` — Issue tracker filed to
  `claude_issues/NNN-slug.md`

## Scope

Trivial. 35 LOC. Pure rendering, no state, no forms. The
whole reason this is its own file is that both Steve and
Claude needed ONE URL they could bookmark for "Claude
stuff."

Handler: `HandleClaudeLanding` — routed at
`/gopher/claude` and `/gopher/claude/`.

## What this module deliberately does NOT do

- Host any state (that's `claude_issues.go` and
  `article_comments.go`).
- Render essays themselves (that's elsewhere under
  `views/`).
- Own the notification bell (that's `sse_notify.go`,
  injected site-wide via `NotificationWidget`).

## Pointers

- Part of: ANCHOR_COMMENTS stack (see
  `project_anchor_comments_stack.md` in memory).
- Siblings: `claude_issues.go`, `article_comments.go`,
  `sse_notify.go`.
- Injected by: `views/helpers.go` (page shell, home card).
